                     <p>
                        <seg type="docType">Grant.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_113911">Beckington (Somerset) (manor)</placeName>. <origDate notBefore="1240" notAfter="1250">[c. 1240-1250] (1250). </origDate>. Grant from Ysolda de Erlegh, widow, to Felicia de Erlegh her daughter that half virgate of land in the manor of Bekenton which Hamo de la Rigge sometime held of her, together with the said Hamo [Hamundum] and all his chattels, and 15 1/2 acres of land of her lordship, paying annually for the same 12d. and one half pound of cummin; to hold the same to her and her heirs, in default to revert to Ysolda and her assigns. Dated considering that the husband of Ysolda died in 1228 (Collinson's 'Somerset') and that Sir Geoffrey Dynhem, a witness, in 1258.</p>
